### Billing Rates API Test File
### Base URL: https://localhost:7001/api/BillingRates

### Variables
@baseUrl = https://localhost:7001
@apiUrl = {{baseUrl}}/api/BillingRates
@token = your_jwt_token_here

### 1. Create a new billing rate table
POST {{apiUrl}}
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Standard Hourly Rates",
  "description": "Standard hourly rates for general maintenance work",
  "rateType": "Flat Fee",
  "baseRate": 75.00,
  "effectiveStartDate": "2025-10-14T00:00:00Z",
  "effectiveEndDate": "2026-12-31T23:59:59Z",
  "isActive": true
}

### 2. Create another billing rate table
POST {{apiUrl}}
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Emergency Service Rates",
  "description": "Premium rates for emergency and after-hours service calls",
  "rateType": "Flat Fee",
  "baseRate": 125.00,
  "effectiveStartDate": "2025-10-14T00:00:00Z",
  "effectiveEndDate": "2026-12-31T23:59:59Z",
  "isActive": true
}

### 3. Get all billing rates
GET {{apiUrl}}
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### 4. Get all active billing rates only
GET {{apiUrl}}?isActive=true
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### 5. Get billing rates by date range
GET {{apiUrl}}?startDate=2025-10-01T00:00:00Z&endDate=2025-12-31T23:59:59Z
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### 6. Get a specific billing rate by ID (replace {id} with actual ID from create response)
GET {{apiUrl}}/{id}
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### 7. Update a billing rate (replace {id} with actual ID)
PUT {{apiUrl}}/{id}
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Updated Standard Hourly Rates",
  "description": "Updated standard hourly rates with new pricing structure",
  "rateType": "Flat Fee",
  "baseRate": 85.00,
  "effectiveStartDate": "2025-10-14T00:00:00Z",
  "effectiveEndDate": "2026-12-31T23:59:59Z",
  "isActive": true
}

### 8. Delete a billing rate (replace {id} with actual ID)
DELETE {{apiUrl}}/{id}
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

